	(layer "F.Cu")
	(descr "Shun Xiang Nuo SMNR4020 magnetic-resin shielded SMD power inductor, 4.0 x 4.0 x 2.0 mm. L1 = SMNR4020-2.2UH (LCSC C135262): 2.2uH +/-20%, Isat 3.4 A, DCR 46 mohm. Land pattern per SXN datasheet p.4 'Recommended Land Pattern': F=0.95 Typ is each pad's SHORT side, G=2.1 Typ is the GAP BETWEEN the pads, H=3.3 Typ is each pad's LONG side. -> pads 0.95 x 3.3 mm, centres at +/-(G+F)/2 = +/-1.525 mm, outer span F+G+F = 4.0 mm (flush with the body edge). This equals the part's own terminals (E=3.3 wide, D=2.1 gap): SXN's land is 1:1 with the electrode, no toe fillet -- do not add one, JLCPCB checks against this pattern. SIZED FOR THE 1.50 A STARTUP INRUSH measured in LTspice with TI's TPS61023 model -- NOT the 0.54 A steady-state current. Do not substitute a 3x3 part.")
	(tags "inductor power 4x4 shielded sxn smnr4020 boost")
